body:
Hey.  
I think this issue (or a variation of it) still exists on Webpack 5.11.1.  
Bundling [RobinBuschmann/sequelize-typescript](https://github.com/RobinBuschmann/sequelize-typescript) produces the following - 

Source: 
```javascript
if (!new.target.isInitialized) {
            throw new model_not_initialized_error_1.ModelNotInitializedError(new.target, `${new.target.name} cannot be instantiated.`);
```

Webpack 5.11.1 output:
```javascript
if (true) {
            throw new model_not_initialized_error_1.ModelNotInitializedError(new.target, `${new.target.name} cannot be instantiated.`);
```

Reported originally in https://github.com/RobinBuschmann/sequelize-typescript/issues/850. 

@sokra should I open a separate issue or should #11310 be reopened?
